23/06/2006
HELSINKI, Finland -- Romania will not bring unsolved problems to the EU after it joins on 1 January 2007, Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu said Thursday (22 June) in Helsinki. 
He met with his Finnish counterpart, Erkki Tuomioja, who voiced positive expectations concerning the upcoming EU enlargement.
Romania is committed to complying with all recommendations in the latest European Commission report, to be fully prepared to join the Union, Ungureanu said. 
"Romania does not want to bring worries into the EU, but wants to bring an opportunity," he added. 
(Rompres - 22/06/06)
